I found my problem is that , my sql limit rowcount.value is dynamic  then in multi thread context serveral selectstatements use the same Limit object , in the below code, the `limit.getRowCountValue()` maybe the other selectstatement setted, so it reads less data
`  @Override
    public boolean next() throws SQLException {
        if (skipAll) {
            return false;
        }
        if (limit.getRowCountValue() < 0) {
            return getMergedResult().next();
        }
        return ++rowNumber <= limit.getRowCountValue() && getMergedResult().next();
    }.`  when i use a static rowcount , it is correct

